Class CircleFinding

  • java.lang.Object
    • craj.CircleFinding

  • public class CircleFinding
extends java.lang.Object
    This class holds the data of a circle finding. It is used to store in which image the circle was found in which coordinate.

        Create a circle finding with the given coordinate, the source image data, the reference circle and the calculated cross value and cross count.
        Parameters:
        x - the x coordinate of the circle finding in the image
        y - the y coordinate of the circle finding in the image
        referenceCircle - the reference circle of this circle finding
        sourceImageData - the image data where the circle finding was found
        pixelCrossValue - the calculated cross value of this circle finding
        pixelCrossCount - the calculated cross count of this circle finding
